Kisii Ward Administrator Evans Nyaoka Rambeka has been handed one-year imprisonment in default for forging academic papers. Kisii Chief Magistrate N. S Lutta convicted him for forging and using a Certificate and a Diploma in Human Resource Management. He was fined Sh450,000 for using forged academic certificates to secure employment as a Ward Administrator. Evans claimed that the documents were genuine and issued by the Kenya Institute of Management. The Ethics and Anti-Corruption Commission conducted investigations and preferred five counts of charges against him which he was convicted on.